[1
Date: Tue, 30 Oct 2001 18:13:49 -0500
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org> &
Source: KPIX online [edited
<http://dailynews.yahoo.com/h/kpix/20011030/lo/1635_1.html>

Anthrax Found in Bay Area Cattle
-------------------------------------------
There's been an anthrax outbreak at a Santa Clara ranch. Health
officials say 21 cattle have died from anthrax infections since
October 20th. Another 120 have been vaccinated. Anthrax occurs
naturally in the ground in California, and experts say there's no
reason to believe this outbreak is related to terrorist attacks.
"At this time we believe that this is a naturally-occurring incidence
of anthrax that comes from the soil," said Santa Clara County
Agriculture Commissioner Greg Van Wassenhove. "Traditionally and
historically, anthrax has been prevalent in California. It's not a
common occurrence, but it's not uncommon, as well."
The dead cattle have been buried. Officials say only people who came
in direct contact with the animals are at risk of infection, and those
people have been given antibiotics.
[Byline: David Mills, KPIX
